This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a technique for improving decentralized stochastic gradient descent (SGD) algorithms. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with decentralized communication. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves quantized communication, cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with control of distributed systems, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training neural networks.
